  <h2>About Trackfriend</h2>
  <div class="row row-cols-1 row-cols-md-3">
    <div class="col mb-4">
      <div class="card">
        <img src="/icons/sleeping_zz.png" class="card-img-top" alt="image of a drawn half moon with a blanket on top, representing wellbeing">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Wellbeing</h5>
          <p class="card-text">Scheduling rest times, keeping track of the amount of rest getting statistics related to your habits will help you get better sleep!</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col mb-4">
      <div class="card">
        <img src="/icons/nutrition.png" class="card-img-top" alt="image of a drawn block note used to plan nutrition">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Nutrition</h5>
          <p class="card-text">Keeping track of your nutrition will now be easy! with an intuitive Interface and easy to set goals it’s kid’s play! set calories to loose, keep track of them and ensure getting an achivement!</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col mb-4">
      <div class="card">
        <img src="/icons/dumbbell.png" class="card-img-top" alt="an image of a drawn heart with a dumbell next to it, representing Fitness">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Fitness</h5>
          <p class="card-text">keeping track of exercies , steps, runs and other outdoors/ indroors activities is easibly achievable with Trackfriend</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
 
    <div class="col mb-4">
      <div class="card">
        <img src="/icons/healthy.png" class="card-img-top" alt="image of a stick figured healthy person.">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Frequently asked questions at trackfriend!</h5>
          <p class="card-text"><b class="text-primary">Q1.</b><strong class="text-primary">How do we use your data?</strong> Trackfriend's data collection aspect is simple! we just keep it to a bare minimum: your <i class="text-info">username</i> and <i class="text-info">password</i>.<small>your passwords are safe and any extra information is just your interest: keeping track of your <i class="text-info">weight</i> and attaching an <i class="text-info">email</i> to your account is completely optional</small></p>
        </div>
